# The first line is called the simple input and is where
# you can put many of the ORCA input arguments
! B3LYP def2-TZVP Opt Freq NormalPrint xyzfile 

# This line tells ORCA to parallelize over 4 CPU cores
%pal nprocs 4 end 

# Here we specify the charge, spin, and coordinates
# Example coordinates are shown for an H2 molecule
*xyz 0 2
N           0.00000000000000      0.00000000000000      0.00000000000000
N           1.18309639330900      0.00000000000000      0.00000000000000
N           2.36619342976983      0.00016493794136      0.00000000000000
*
